[2026-03-18T17:38:49.354Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Execute this requirement immediately without asking questions.\n\n## REQUIREMENT\n\n# Hash-chain audit entries for tamper evidence\n\n## Metadata\n- **Category**: functionality\n- **Effort**: Unknown (4/3)\n- **Impact**: Unknown (7/3)\n- **Scan Type**: insight_synth\n- **Generated**: 3/18/2026, 9:56:47 AM\n\n## Description\nAuditLog enforces append-only at the code level (no UPDATE/DELETE exposed), but AuditRetentionPolicy.getDb() exposes raw SQLite access, and anyone with file access can modify audit.db. Add a prev_hash column where each row includes SHA-256(prev_hash + current_row_data). This creates a hash chain � any tampering breaks the chain and is detectable by a verify() scan. The derivation is cheap (single SHA-256 per insert) and can reuse existing shared/crypto.ts primitives.\n\n## Reasoning\nFor real compliance (SOC2, HIPAA, GDPR), append-only semantics must be verifiable, not just trusted. The getDb() escape hatch for retention already proves the append-only contract is permeable. A hash chain makes the audit log self-proving: an auditor can run verify() and mathematically confirm no records were altered. This elevates compliance from best-effort to cryptographically provable.\n\n\n## Recommended Skills\n\nUse Claude Code skills as appropriate for implementation guidance. Check `.claude/skills/` directory for available skills.\n\n## Notes\n\nThis requirement was generated from an AI-evaluated project idea. No specific goal is associated with this idea.\n\n## DURING IMPLEMENTATION\n\n- Use `get_memory` MCP tool when you encounter unfamiliar code or need context about patterns/files\n- Use `report_progress` MCP tool at each major phase (analyzing, planning, implementing, testing, validating)\n- Use `get_related_tasks` MCP tool before modifying shared files to check for parallel task conflicts\n\n## AFTER IMPLEMENTATION\n\n1. Log your implementation using the `log_implementation` MCP tool with:\n   - requirementName: the requirement filename (without .md)\n   - title: 2-6 word summary\n   - overview: 1-2 paragraphs describing what was done\n   - category: one of feature/bugfix/refactor/performance/security/infrastructure/ui/docs/test\n   - patternsApplied: comma-separated patterns used (e.g. \"repository pattern, debounce, memoization\")\n\n2. Verify: `npx tsc --noEmit` (fix any type errors)\n\nBegin implementation now."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eb60ec7e-10ee-466d-923c-20caac10d112","uuid":"f2077db8-ddc6-4679-85b1-5a452f9d5758","timestamp":"2026-03-18T17:38:49.270Z","isSynthetic":true}
